Robert  Acri (October 1, 1918 – July 25, 2013) was an American jazz pianist.
Robert  Acri (October 1, 1918 – July 25, 2013) was an American jazz pianist.
Acri graduated from Austin High School in Chicago.
Acri graduated from Austin High School in Chicago.
During his career he played in the radio orchestras of NBC and ABC, as well as in the House Band of the Chicago nightclub Mister Kelly's.
He ended his career as the leader of the house band at the Cantina Room of the Continental Plaza Hotel.
Acri released two solo albums of instrumental tracks in 2001 and 2004.
